quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
35,4,"(O Prophet), (there is nothing novel in it) if they cry lies to you; {1} Messengers before you were also cried lies to. To Allah shall all matters be sent back. {2}",footnotes:1:“If they deny”: If they do not believe that there is no one worthy of worship but Allah
35,5,"O people, assuredly Allah's promise is true. {1} So let the life of the world not delude you, {2} and let not the Deluder delude you concerning Allah. {3}",footnotes:1:“The promise” implies the promise of the Hereafter to which allusion was made in the preceding sentence
35,6,"Surely Satan is an enemy to you. Therefore, do take him as an enemy. He calls his followers to his way so that they may be among the inmates of the Fire."
35,7,"A severe chastisement lies in store for those that disbelieve, {1} but there is pardon and a great reward for those that believe and work righteous deeds. {2}",footnotes:1:“Those who disbelieve”: those who will refuse to believe in this invitation of Allah’s Book and His Messenger.That is
35,8,"(How {1} awful is the straying of the person) for whom his evil deed has been embellished so that it looks fair to him? {2} The fact is that Allah causes whomsoever He will to fall into error and shows the Right Way to whomsoever He will. So, (O Prophet), let not your life go to waste sorrowing over them. {3} Allah is well aware of all that they do. {4}",footnotes:1:(Verses 3-7) were addressed to the common people. In this paragraph mention has been made of the standard bearers of error and deviation
35,9,"It is Allah Who sends forth winds which then set the clouds in motion, which We drive to some dead land giving a fresh life to earth after it had become dead. Such will be the resurrection of the dead. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
35,10,"He who seeks glory, let him know that all glory belongs to Allah alone. {1} To Him do good words go up, and righteous action uplifts them. {2} But those who contrive evil deeds, {3} a severe punishment lies in store for them, and their contriving will come to naught.",footnotes:1:This is the real means of attaining the honor. In the sight of Allah
35,11,"Allah {1} created you from dust, then from a drop of sperm, {2} then He made you into pairs. No female conceives, nor delivers (a child) except with His knowledge. None is given a long life nor is any diminished in his life but it is written in a Book. {3} Surely that is quite easy for Allah. {4}",footnotes:1:From here again the discourse is directed to the common people.That is
